  I don't see the point of waiting on this spawn, let alone a queue 3 people deep when it's an 18 hour spawn that can skip a spawn.  That's just masochistic, and not in a healthy way.<br>
<br>
  Basically what I'm saying is that when I was camping Stormfeather, way back when, it was generally recognised by the people there at the time as a camp, and those few who disagreed would be welcome to <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> try</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> and outdamage me.  If they did... hey, it happens, I'd be pissed but life goes on.  I can only dictate how <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> I</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> behave, I don't really feel I have the right to impose my code of behaviour on others.<br>
<br>
  Basically it comes down to the individual player.  Crypte did not see anything wrong with what he did.  That's fine.  It's also fine that some people disagree, and I'm sure there will be consequences for Cryptes actions.<br>
